# Figma Design Reference

## Source of Truth

- The source of truth for **all** UI is this Figma file:
  https://www.figma.com/design/DQt7HK12DNJbK7dMoB1ju7/Full-E-Commerce-Website-UI-UX-Design--Community---Copy-?node-id=1-3&p=f
- Never assume or invent design values — always pull from Figma before writing any code.

## Workflow — Follow This Every Time

1. Use the **figma-context-mcp** tool to call `get_figma_data` on the Figma URL above.
2. List all available frames and infer the most relevant one based on what is being built (e.g. "product listing" → find a frame with a matching name or intent).
3. If multiple frames could match, list them and pick the most specific one.
4. Extract **exact** spacing, colors, typography, and layout from the matched frame.
5. Map extracted design tokens to Tailwind config values before writing any component code.
6. Only then write the component or page.

## Design Token Extraction

- Map Figma color styles → `tailwind.config.ts` under `theme.extend.colors`
- Map Figma text styles → `theme.extend.fontSize` and `theme.extend.fontFamily`
- Map Figma spacing/padding values → `theme.extend.spacing`
- Never use arbitrary Tailwind values (e.g. `w-[347px]`) — define named tokens instead.

## Mobile View

- The Figma file only contains desktop designs.
- Mobile views must be designed independently using your own judgment.
- Mobile breakpoint is `sm` (640px) — design for it after desktop is complete.

## Stack

- React + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS
- Reuse components from `src/components/` before creating new ones.
- Match all Tailwind tokens to Figma design tokens (colors, spacing, font sizes).